[SN]TITLE[SN]
Search for brightest Wales Sport Awards stars begins

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The search for the brightest Welsh sport stars of 2015 has begun.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Hosted by BBC Wales and Sport Wales, The Wales Sport Awards recognise the achievements of elite athletes and those involved at grassroots level.
Members of the public can get involved by nominating their local sporting heroes from 1 September.
The winners will be announced at a ceremony in Cardiff on 7 December, alongside the BBC Cymru Wales Sports Personality of the Year prize.
BBC Wales director, Rhodri Talfan Davies, said: "The Wales Sport Awards event is an opportunity to look back on the year and recognise the dedicated individuals on all levels who have contributed to make Wales a sporting nation that punches well above its weight."
Sport Wales chairwoman, Prof Laura McAllister, added: "Sport is part of the fabric of Welsh life and recognising the impact of people who often go unnoticed is vital if we are to cement our importance at the heart of communities in Wales."
